.TH "rtrs_clt_get_permit" 9 "rtrs_clt_get_permit" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rtrs_clt_get_permit \- allocates permit for future RDMA operation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct rtrs_permit *" rtrs_clt_get_permit
.BI "(struct rtrs_clt *clt "  ","
.BI "enum rtrs_clt_con_type con_type "  ","
.BI "int can_wait "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "clt" 12
Current session
.IP "con_type" 12
Type of connection to use with the permit
.IP "can_wait" 12
Wait type
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocates permit for the following RDMA operation.  Permit is used
to preallocate all resources and to propagate memory pressure
up earlier.
.SH "CONTEXT"
Can sleep if \fIwait\fP == RTRS_TAG_WAIT
